value.name: Teenage Fairytale Dropouts
value.overview:
Three best friends, Jeremiah, Trafalgar, and Fury, who are all relatives of iconic fairy-tale characters, all live through a tough life as teenagers and are determined to be themselves, despite their parents' orders and their fairy tale origins.

Although rating well in Australia, one of the countries which co-produced the series, it did not do well elsewhere. In 2017 the distribution rights were acquired by Bejuba! Entertainment who have renamed it "Awesome Magical Tales". As of 2019 it is still screening in Australia under its original title.
